main event: A single, round object the size of a star was observed bobbing in the sky over Seattle, Washington for 30 minutes.
interesting points: The object was observed by both civilian and military witnesses.
The area had heavy balloon activity, suggesting the object was likely a balloon.
The description and duration of the sighting are consistent with a balloon observation.
The report indicates that no photographs were taken of the object.
The sighting occurred on July 23, 1952 at 9:00 PM GMT.
sighted object: a single, round object the size of a star
